The book drawing is annoying because:

* the three gearsets are nested visually
* the shafts are drawn with overlapping vertical and horizontal segments
* brakes and clutches are shown as little stubs without obvious node labels
* the freewheels complicate the logic because they act only in one torque direction

But underneath all that mess, the W5A-580 is actually a pretty logical chain of three simple planetary sets.

It is much more readable once converted into node relationships instead of trying to decode the picture directly.

